AB  - This paper presents two new ways of deriving the maximum-likelihood estimators of subsystems of a simultaneous-equation model. The two derivations are based on an expression of the likelihood function in terms of the reduced-form parameters; and they give rise to two alternative versions of the estimating equations. These equations are compared with those that are derivable from the concentrated likelihood function of Koopmans and Hood, and the equivalence of the three sets of estimating equations is demonstrated.
